<br>
- Can mages effectively solo 1-60 or are they more group dependent?<br>
<br>
- When soloing does a mage just chain summon pets or can they solo useing 1 pet a nuke or 2 and a few heals and be at 60% or greater mana by end of fight (i.e. not 5-10 mins of dt after each fight)?<br>
<br>
- On that subject, can mages solo yellow cons and higher for several % XP per kill or do they mow through dblues or struggle with dblues?<br>
<br>
Finally, in everyones honest opinion, am I right for the mage class thinking that they can solo 1-60 with little dt between fights or should I go the Necro/Shaman route (which I would rather not)? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=krankenthegnome>Kranken the Gnome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 319<br> <font color=#333333>(12/2/02 1:27:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=429.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://saedyan.freesehttp://pages.prodigy.net/cohmsford/america.gifrvers.com/images/pstgif.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Wondering if the Mage can be the soloist class I want...</span><hr size=1> Yes<br>
<br>
Can do either, though at about 50 chaincasting becomes far and away more efficient.<br>
<br>
Up until about 40 yes, then it's better to stick to blues.. blues are generally better exp to solo anyway.<br>
<br>
<br>
I always fought with minimal to no downtime all the way to 60... just be aware that post 60 group exp absolutely blows away anything you can get solo, and by 65 you won't be able to solo blue cons anyway without a tremendous amount of effort. <p>------------<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Kranken<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->62 Arch Mage<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Xev<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->&quot;Where's my pet..?&quot;</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=solairous>Solairous</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(12/2/02 6:26:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=429.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_thumbsup.gif" align=absmiddle>  thank......</span><hr size=1> ok, thanks <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  that is what I was hoping for, chainsummoning pets sounds mana intensive which would be lots of downtime. Just one last thing, with KEI does one become better than the other? I have enough pp to have my mage almost perma-KEIed. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=krankenthegnome>Kranken the Gnome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 321<br> <font color=#333333>(12/3/02 3:32:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=429.top